# Project‑wide rules for Cursor AI agents
LANG=en
STACK=NextJS+TypeScript+Tailwind+Shadcn/UI
PKG_MGR=pnpm

# Branding
BRAND=Vidy is the only user-facing brand. Never expose underlying providers (fal.ai, fal-ai/* slugs, OpenAI, ElevenLabs, Topaz, etc.) in any user-visible UI string, FAQ, marketing copy, error message, OG/meta tag, llms.txt, or page metadata. Internal code (lib/, env vars, model registry slugs) may reference them; UI must not.
PROVIDER_HIDING_PATTERNS:
  - Strip the `fal-ai/` prefix when rendering any model slug; prefer FalModel.displayName.
  - Any progress / status / error message: name the action ("Generating…", "Calling AI…"), never the provider.
  - Marketing copy and FAQ: refer to "Vidy", "Vidy's models", "our agent", or use neutral product names (Veo, Kling, Flux, Ideogram, etc.) — those are model brands users recognize, not the provider routing.

# UI
STYLE_GUIDE:
  - No cheesy violet gradients. Glass aesthetic: bg-white/60, ring-1 ring-black/5, rounded-3xl, backdrop-blur-md.
  - Black primary buttons, rounded-2xl. White outline secondary.
  - Use existing Shadcn-style components in src/components/ui/ before adding new ones.
  - When in doubt about a UI rewrite, do NOT replace user-built UIs. Modify in place; surgical edits only.
  - Keep hero section ≤ 60 vh.


# Auth
AUTH=Supabase OAuth (Google) + email/password

# Storage
MEDIA_STORAGE=Supabase Storage -> bucket `videos`

# Payments
PAYMENTS=Stripe Subscriptions + Usage‑based credits
CREDIT_TABLE=credits(model_id, feature, balance)

# Analytics
ANALYTICS=Firebase GA4 (log all CTA clicks, generation events, credit debits)

# Build & Deploy
DEPLOY=Vercel
CI=GitHub Actions (`pnpm install --frozen-lockfile && pnpm build`)
In everytime do not start with a new dev server, kill all and start new one, so we will use it :3000 port. 

# Lint / Format
ESLINT=yes
PRETTIER=yes 